Definition at line 223 of file relic_fpx.h.

◆ fp54_t

typedef fp18_t fp54_t[3]

Represents a 54-degree extension field element.

This extension is constructed with the basis {1, u, u^2}, where u^3 = t is an adjoined root in the underlying octdecic extension.

Definition at line 231 of file relic_fpx.h.

◆ fp18_test_cyc()

int fp18_test_cyc ( const fp18_t a)

Tests if an octdecic extension field element belongs to the cyclotomic subgroup.

A cyclotomic element is one raised to the (p^9 - 1)(p^3 + 1)-th power.

Parameters
[in]a- the octdecic extension field element to test.
Returns
1 if the extension field element is in the subgroup, 0 otherwise.

◆ fp54_inv_cyc()

void fp54_inv_cyc ( fp54_t c,
const fp54_t a )

Computes the inverse of a cyclotomic 54-extension field element.

For unitary elements, this is equivalent to computing the conjugate. A unitary element is one previously raised to the (p^24 - 1)-th power.

Parameters
